{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"@preconcurrency","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSViewControllerRepresentable","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/Body-swift.associatedtype","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP4BodyQa","text":"Body","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" == ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5NeverO","text":"Never","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/NSViewControllerRepresentable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance to create and manage an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/appkit\/nsviewcontroller","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object in your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI interface. Adopt this protocol in one of your app’s custom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instances, and use its methods to create, update, and tear down your view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controller. The creation and update processes parallel the behavior of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI views, and you use them to configure your view controller with your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"app’s current state information. Use the teardown process to remove your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view controller cleanly from your OpenSwiftUI. For example, you might use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"teardown process to notify other objects that the view controller is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disappearing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add your view controller into your OpenSwiftUI interface, create your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSViewControllerRepresentable"},{"type":"text","text":" instance and add it to your OpenSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interface. The system calls the methods of your custom instance at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appropriate times."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The system doesn’t automatically communicate changes occurring within your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view controller to other parts of your OpenSwiftUI interface. When you want your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view controller to coordinate with other OpenSwiftUI views, you must provide a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/NSViewControllerRepresentable\/Coordinator","isActive":true},{"text":" instance to facilitate those","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interactions. For example, you use a coordinator to forward target-action","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and delegate messages from your view controller to any OpenSwiftUI views.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"warning","type":"aside","name":"Warning","content":[{"inlineConte